=== DOCUMENTATION FOR TARGET: CPU ===

<target_short_dscr>:
CPU system registers.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
General Purpose Register
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
General purpose 8 times 32-bit registers for software development and debug.
Note: This register is only reset by the device's reset input, i.e. it is not affected by soft reset!
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Reset Settings
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this field to generate a soft reset for the VCore. This field will be cleared when the reset has taken effect.
It is possible to protect the blocks of vcore system with protection bits.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: VCore is not reset
1: Initiate soft reset of the VCore and the reset will get cleared after the reset process is done.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This register performs warm reset of Core 0 of ARM Processor inside Vcore system.
Self clearing field at the end of warm reset.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 - Normal operation
1 - Perform warm reset of core 0 (Self clears at the end of reset).
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This register performs warm reset of Core 1 of ARM Processor inside Vcore system.
Self clearing field at the end of warm reset.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 - Normal operation
1 - Perform warm reset of core 1 (Self clears at the end of reset).
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This single, cluster-wide field resets the integrated CoreSight components that connect to the external PCLK domain, such as debug logic.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 - No reset to debug interface due to this register.
1 - Reset applied to debug interface due to this register.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field resets the L2 cache in CPU of VCORE to be in reset.
This block auto-clears when reset of L2 is complete.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 - Put the CPU L2 cache in reset (auto-clear at the end of reset).
0 - CPU L2 cache is not in reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field resets the DDR Memory in the Vcore Sub-system.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 - DDR Memory is in reset (self - clears when DDR reset is done).
0 - DDR Memory is not in reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field forces the WDT block in APB into reset.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 - Force WDT into Reset.
0 - Bring WDT out of reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field performs a cold reset (includes debug logic of core 0) of CPU Core 0.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 -  Core 0 of CPU is in cold reset
0  - Core 0 of CPU is not in cold reset
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field performs a cold reset (includes debug logic of core 1) of CPU Core 1.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 -  Core 1 of CPU is in cold reset
0  - Core 1 of CPU is not in cold reset
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field resets the GIC Block.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 - Do not reset GIC block.
1 - Put GIC Block in reset.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
This register contains fields that protect certain blocks from resets.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field protects the VCORE from System reset.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: System reset also causes VCore to go into reset.
1: Vcore is protected from System Reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field protects AMBA from Vcore Reset, WDT reset.
This field also protects AXI from VCORE_RST_FORCE (that comes from GCB target)
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No Protection is applied to AMBA
1: AMBA is protected from Vcore Reset and Watch dog Timeout reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this field to protect Watch dog Timer from Watch dog Timeout reset and Vcore Soft Reset (VCORE_RST Register).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No reset protection to Watch Dog Timer block.
1: WDT block is protected from VCORE Soft Reset and its own timeout.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field protects the integrated coresight components from: Watchdog timer reset, Vcore Soft Reset (VCORE_RST Register Field), Vcore Cold Reset (CPU_CORE_x_COLD_RST).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : No protection to processor's debug logic.
1 : Protection applied to processor debug logic from Watch dog timeout, Vcore soft reset, Vcore Cold Reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
By default, GIC is reset when both the cores of CPU are cold reset. 
However, this field protects GIC from getting reset in such cases.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : No protection to GIC when both the cores of CPU are cold reset.
1 : GIC is protected from reset when both the cores of CPU are cold reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field protects the Watch-dog timer block in the vcore-system from its own timeout.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
1 - Protect the Vcore's WDT from its own timeout.
0 - resets the WDT block as well from VCORE's Watch-dog timer timeout.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This register contains the status indication to indicate that VCORE has been reset because of WDT.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : Watch dog timer timeout is not the cause for Vcore Reset. 
1 : Watch dog timer timeout is the cause for vcore reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
GIC has been reset due to either ecc_fatal (Unrecoverable fatal error) indication from SRAMS inside it or
due to fatal errors (SLVERR/DECERR) received from accessing DDR Memory.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : GIC has not been reset due to the mentioned causes.
1 : GIC has been reset due to ecc_fatal error from SRAMS.
2 : GIC has been reset due to SLVERR/DECERR received from accessing DDR Memory.
3 : GIC has been reset due to ecc_fatal error from SRAMS and there was also error on accessing DDR.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
By default L2 is reset when both cores of processor are cold reset. This register protects from such auto resetting of L2
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 - No protection from auto reset of L2.
1 - Protect L2 when both cores of processor are cold reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This protection bits protects GIC from resetting itself.
This occurs when there is any error on transaction towards the AXI Master port of the GIC.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
'0' : GIC is not protected from a reset by itself.
'1': GIC is protected from a reset by itself.
